   Examinations: Compliance
     __________________________________________________________________


   Two men sitting in school desks with computers The FDIC has enforcement
   responsibilities for various consumer protection, fair lending, and
   certain related regulations for the financial institutions it
   supervises.

   Compliance Examination Manual

   The FDIC's manual for field examiners who conduct Compliance and
   Community Reinvestment Act (CRA) examinations and for regional office
   and Washington office staffs who process examination reports and
   related documents.

   Compliance Examination Planning Documents

   About to undergo a Compliance or Community Reinvestment Act (CRA)
   examination? Here are all the reference materials you need to prepare
   for the examination.

   RESPA Escrow Program

   A computer spreadsheet used by banking industry professionals to
   determine if their financial institution is properly calculating and
   disclosing escrow account information as required under the Real Estate
   Settlement Procedures Act.

   Mortgage Loan Prequalifications

   A 14-page guide for banks and financial institutions that answers
   questions that lenders and consumers ask about mortgage loan
   prequalification programs.
   (99Kb PDF file - PDF help or hard copy)
